Popular South African DJ Capital will hit the decks at Carnival City s Bru s to entertain guests on Saturday. The Club 808 co-host and Touch Central radio host will perform from 10am and there is no cost to join the party. DJ Capital, who started his career in the music industry as a rapper, entered the world of radio presenting in 2011 after landing an opportunity to work at radio stations Umhlobo Wenene FM. The three-time SA Hip-Hop Award nominee has held his own alongside greats such as Deadmau5, AfroJack, Usher and Eminem s former deejay, DJ Green Lantern